<br>
-QUI affects your weapon delay, and how much style bonus you get (Style bonus decreases with increasing QUI).<br>
<br>
-QUI does NOT affect base damage.<br>
<br>
So, right away, it's evident that your DPS increases with QUI if all you do are unstyled attacks.<br>
<br>
Now, when you style, increased QUI decreases <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>how much</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> style bonus you get.  So if your class can kill an opponent in 2 swings, it is in your best interest to have low Quickness.  However, if your class depends on many fast attacks to kill an opponent, then you gain more DPS from your base attacks, than you lose from your style bonus.<br>
<br>
Hopefully that makes sense, without relying on all the equations and numbers floating around. <p>Kerrec Snowmane<br>
Mercenary Team Lead<br>
R6L2, Palomides.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vasagh>Vasagh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 88<br> <font color=#000000>(10/6/03 1:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=362.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Capping quick? yes? no?</span><hr size=1> Everything kerrec said is correct except this little part <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
&quot;Now, when you style, increased QUI decreases how much style bonus you get.&quot;<br>
<br>
This is correct but over a number of hits it's the same total because the style dps is not affected by qui/haste.<br>
<br>
&quot;So if your class can kill an opponent in 2 swings, it is in your best interest to have low Quickness.&quot;<br>
<br>
1 swing. If you swing 2 or more, higher quickness setup outdamages. I'll give a small example to demonstrate.<br>
<br>
With higher quickness your 2nd hit comes faster, so not only it catches up but surpasses the total damage inflicted in the shortest possible time.<br>
<br>
Or in numbers:<br>
<br>
5spd swing. base dmg 200, style bonus +100 (20 dps) .<br>
1st swing 300 dmg + 2nd swing 300 dmg at time 5second.<br>
Total 600 dmg at 5seconds.<br>
<br>
2.5 spd swing. base dmg 200, style bonus +50 (20 dps).<br>
1st swing 250 dmg + 2nd swing 250 dmg at time 2.5second.<br>
Total 500 dmg at 2.5 seconds or 750 at 5seconds.<br>
<br>
<br>
There are times where on the 2nd hit a slower swing (without qui/haste) can surpass the total dmg of the high qui setup but it also takes a *longer* period to register those hits. <br>
For example:<br>
<br>
4 spd swing base dmg 200, style bonus +200 (50 dps)<br>
1st swing 400 dmg + 2nd swing 400 dmg at time 4second.<br>
Total 800 dmg at 4 seconds.<br>
<br>
3 spd swing base dmg 200, style bonus +150 (50 dps)<br>
1st swing 350 dmg + 2nd swing 350 dmg at time 3second.<br>
Total 700 dmg at 3 seconds.<br>
<br>
In this example we see the no-quickness setup do 100 dmg more in 2hits. But the high-qui setup is outdamaging it by getting 700 dmg in 3seconds, while the no-quickness setup needs 1 more second to outdamage it and it will fall behind more and more as it takes longer to kill your target. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vasagh>Vasagh</A> at: 10/6/03 1:29 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zyke>Zyke</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#000000>(10/6/03 2:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=362.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Capping quick? yes? no?</span><hr size=1> Yes.<br>
