<br>
1 is your frontload damage because of higher quick if you style on your first hit you will hit for a little less. We got flurry for a reason so use it there.<br>
<br>
2 You will not get as much bang out of a full end bar as with 0 quickness. End useage does'nt scale up with quickness or haste so you end up doing less style damage overall.<br>
<br>
Conclusion <br>
Is it worth it to cap quickness ?? <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:lime;font-family:courier;font-size:large;">YES</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
You get more damage overall, get less delay between your attacks wich in turn gives you much more reactive styles opportunities. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:black;font-family:georgia;font-size:x-small;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Nalfen Silverblade</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
